
StringTokenizer Class

1. What is StringTokenizer in Java? How do you create a StringTokenizer object?
-->Answer:
      StringTokenizer (java.util.StringTokenizer) is a legacy class used to split a string into tokens using a delimiter.
      
      Import
      
      import java.util.StringTokenizer;
      
      Example
      
      import java.util.StringTokenizer;
      
      public class Main {
          public static void main(String[] args) {
      
              StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer("Java Python C++");
      
              while(st.hasMoreTokens()) {
                  System.out.println(st.nextToken());
              }
          }
      }

Output :
    Java
    Python
    C++





2. Important methods of StringTokenizer?
-->
| Method              | Description                   |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| `hasMoreTokens()`   | Checks if more tokens exist   |
| `nextToken()`       | Returns next token            |
| `countTokens()`     | Returns remaining token count |
| `hasMoreElements()` | Same as hasMoreTokens()       |
| `nextElement()`     | Returns next token as Object  |

Example :
    StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer("Java Python C");
    
    System.out.println(st.countTokens());
    
    while(st.hasMoreTokens()) {
        System.out.println(st.nextToken());
    }




3. Difference between StringTokenizer, split(), and Scanner?
-->
| StringTokenizer   | split()       | Scanner                  |
| ----------------- | ------------- | ------------------------ |
| Legacy class      | String method | Input class              |
| Faster            | Uses Regex    | Reads user input         |
| Doesn't use Regex | Uses Regex    | Reads from keyboard/file |
| Less flexible     | Flexible      | Best for input           |
